                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.92/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-19T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Your 81, September 17, 4 p.m. On September 19 the Thai Minister called at his
                    request on an officer of the Department and presented an <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="88" xml:id="d160fn88">Not printed.</note> in reply to the oral
                    communication made to the Thai Minister here on September 11.<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d160fn89">See telegram No. 46, September 11, 5 p.m., to the Minister
                        in Thailand, <ref target="#pg_107">p. 107</ref>.</note> The officer of the
                    Department said, in response to the Thai Minister’s request, that he would be
                    glad to bring the Thai <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to the attention of
                    the Secretary of State. The officer of the Department restated to the Thai
                    Minister briefly the views expressed in the Department’s 37, August 21, 6 p.m.,
                    and 46, September 11, 5 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
